  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, the monsoon rains are perfect for cozying up with a warm cup of tea, what's your go to comfort this season?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tea is my favorite too, but I always add a spoon of jaggery. It makes me feel warm. But honestly, I’ve been too stressed about my exams to really enjoy it. Yesterday I even forgot to add the tea leaves! 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That happens to everyone. Stress makes us forget small things. Jaggery in tea sounds lovely, it's a sweet comfort. How are you feeling today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly, I’m still feeling kind of off. I made a big mistake in my study group today—mixed up two important drug dosages. Everyone laughed, but I just wanted to disappear. It's so embarrassing. 😬"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that, mistakes happen, and it's tough when they feel so public. But you're not alone in this; we all slip sometimes. What helps you feel better after a moment like that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually take a walk or listen to some old ghazals to calm my mind. But today I just sat in my room, hugging my dog. He doesn’t judge me, at least. 😅 Do you ever feel like you’re the only one messing up?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, I do, it feels heavy when others seem so sure. But here’s the thing: everyone messes up, even if they don’t show it. What’s one small thing you did well today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm… I think I finally finished organizing my study notes for the week. It wasn’t perfect, but at least I got it done without any distractions. Small wins, right? 🙃"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, that’s a real win, getting it done is what matters. Distraction free progress is tough to come by! What’s next on your study plan?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tomorrow I have a mock test—cardiovascular section. I’m so nervous I might mix up the dosages again! But I’ll try to take deep breaths and think of my dog, you know? 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a good plan, deep breaths and thinking of your dog can really help. Mock tests are tough, but each one helps you grow stronger. What’s your go to mantra before starting?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually say, \"One question at a time, no rushing.\" But today I added something new: \"Even dogs make mistakes, but they keep wagging their tails.\" 😅 It helps me laugh at myself a little. I think that's all for today—mock test tomorrow, need to rest. Thank you for listening, Maya."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You’re doing great, adding a little humor helps a lot. Rest well, and remember, your dog’s proud of you. How did your mock test go?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly, it went better than I expected! I didn’t mix up any dosages, and I even finished a few minutes early. Maybe the dog mantra worked. 😊 But I’m still tired—need to sleep. Thank you again, Maya. Good night!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great, finishing early is a win! The dog mantra clearly works. Sleep well, Aarti. See you soon!"
    }
  ],
